<br>
Now, last night a Enchanter in my guild solo'd a lvl 65 Mob.  I think it is awesome, but it also could have a affect on the game because if all enchanters started soloing, who would mez the mobs in groups.  When Mages used to solo like this we were overpowered.  So then what does that makes a enchanter.  <br>
<br>
Oh and for those people who say &quot;well we are damage dealers&quot;...who you think does more damage....a enchanter that can kill a level 65 Mob or a Mage?  Who you think they want in groups first...a Enchanter or Mage?  <br>
<br>
YES! we have made improvements, but so has every class.  Also, every class that could solo before still can, except a Mage.  And Yanburn says we can solo when we start fighting Elementals.  Well I havent seen none yet.  And if we were giving a Mez, why didnt the Beta Testers ask for a root just incase Mez failed or wore off.  I dont know about yall but these mobs hit too hard to be trying to cast gate.  For those who said if &quot;Mages got slow or root we would be overpowered&quot;...what do you have to say about the other classes that have all these abilities and can solo.  Wouldnt you call that overpowered?<br>
<br>
We were giving good damage dealing capabilities but now I just fill handicapped.  Used to be able to do something, but now I cant.  <br>
<br>
Immlazen<br>
