<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Increased elemental hitpoints:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  useful soloing, not overpowering in groups, but could it be enough?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Adding mild slow to Earth:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  20-25% slow might tip balance, adds to group appeal, using Earth has other consequences that help balance it<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Summon slow proc weapon:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Similar to above, may be less balanced since any pet<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Increased damage mitigation:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Unlikely to be sufficient, pales in comparison to even modest slow<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Summoned Shield with heal proc:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Unlikely to be sufficient, pales in comparison to even modest slow, balanced by loss of dual wield<br>
<br>
Perhaps some combination of the above might be sufficient.<br>
<br>
Alternately, charm summoned might be our key to soloability, although I see no evidence of this.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think something like a 15% slow for GV:E, and 25% slow for 65 Earth is the simplest and most direct solution.  However, this is more symptomatic of the enormous power of slow than it is thematic for mages.<br>
<br>
If rangers can have some lame ass slow for no good reason that I can tell, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">and</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> it would solve soloability for mages, then I see no reason that our two best earth pets can't have a slow component on their root.<br>
<br>
