<br>
1) Functions similarly to slow in that it mitigates the damage output of the opponent<br>
2) Modifies an existing power rather than adding an entirely new capability to mages<br>
3) As a separate effect from slow, it stacks with slow, although weakly<br>
4) It effects casters, which slow does not<br>
5) It is in theory available to level 61 mages<br>
6) Does not involve adding a new spell<br>
7) Can be easily fine-tuned by the developers in case of unintended consequences<br>
8) Single point fix<br>
<br>
The problem appears to be that many mobs are effectively immune to air stun.  Just as some &quot;unrootable&quot; mobs can be rooted by earth, it is entirely plausible that &quot;unstunnable&quot; mobs could be stunned by air.  If air stun were effective, it would also add specific group value to mages.  Once a slower is grouped, a mage could provide mitigation on top of that, in a form not available to other classes.<br>
<br>
How can this be accomplished without being overpowering?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=razdaleblack>Razdaleblack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 5:46:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Those Darned Soloers...</span><hr size=1> Whatever the solution for us soloing post 60 is it'll likely have to meet many criteria.<br>
<br>
-Needs to be reasonably effective most of the time along the lines of our normal soloing methods. (No quad kiting likely)<br>
-Not stack so well in groups to be overpowering.<br>
-Probably be based on a current ability or a weak version of someone elses.<br>
-Be useable in PoP by mages at 61.<br>
-Etc.<br>
<br>
I do miss soloing. The idea of the super stunning air pet is interesting. It would certainly allow us a better chance at soloing. I think it might be a little overpowered in groups with a slower though. If it were to stick even half the time that would reduce the mobs output to 50% of it's capability. With a good slow on the mob it wouldn't stack perfectly of course but you'd likely be able to cut the mobs damage down by as much as 90% or so on stunnable mobs. Perhaps if this route was used slowed mobs could be tagged immune to pet stun.<br>
<br>
More reasonable I think we're left with summoned weapons with useful procs and the 51 air pet as our most obvious canidates to push. I really like the idea of air pet being able to mitigate more damage through higher AC etc.. That would be the least likely change to tread on other classes turf, or overpower us in groups. <br>
<br>
Any slow, even a weak non stacking one, will likely bring out the trolls with their howls for nerf bats. Snare probably the same thing though either certainly would be helpful to us when mezzing those high lvl elementals. Of course if the snare or slow was on a pet weapon vs regular spells it would ease our aggro issues so we could really nuke with impunity. Soloability increased, but pet still would need to be able to mitigate damage long enough for us to nuke the mob down. Hmmm. Pet weapons with these abilities would also allow us to bypass the problems of us drawing aggro from these spells as squishy casters with no defensive spell lines!<br>
<br>
PoP fights are supposed to be fast and furious. The best exp I've had so far in Tier one was Duoed with a Shammy in PoN. A tick per kill, fights lasted around 90 secs. No mana issues with Burnt wood staff and a few sirroco averaged 4-5k from nukes dependant on resists. 90 secs seems a little long for a duo but I was really conserving mana and we were chain pulling. (I love making a blue every 15 minutes at 5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . If we could keep a pet alive for 60-90 secs with healing and damage mitigation and still be able to nuke we could go solo while LFG. It would be inefficient. Require 3/4's of a mana pool or so but would be an option at least. All of this is of course assuming Sony really cares that we can't solo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pyraxis>pyraxis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 10:35:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Those Darned Soloers...</span><hr size=1> In order for a super stunner air pet to be overpowering in a group with a slower, we would need to be invited into a group with a slower. I think the big problem is that we *aren't* getting invited into groups, and we *can't* solo. If we weren't having group issues, the lack of solo capabilities wouldn't be an issue at all, and we wouldn't be crying for something to help us. But because we are having issues with both factors, that's causing some of us to not want to play anymore. <br>
<br>
Pyraxis, 58th Conjurer<br>
Karana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 744<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 11:20:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Those Darned Soloers...</span><hr size=1> I tried soloing a spider (I forget the name offhand) near the Graveyard in PoN.  Using IR chaining, I got the thing to 20% before I got a root break.  No way to channel a new pet through hits of 150-250, so I was forced to zone.  I don't know what these spiders con at 65, but I can't say that soloing them with 57 Earth pets is the most reliable way to do it.  Add a second chaining magician, and it's cake though.<br>
<br>
If I had 65 Earth (sweet pet, has a negative resist modifier on its root spell), or Malosinia, or BO 5, it might be more doable.  Certainly getting Quick Summoning maxed will help, as could Combat Agility, Channeling Focus, and a few other AA skills.<br>
<br>
I'm seriously considering going heavy on AA's before 61, to be better prepared for the rigors of soloing while lfg.  Or focus on high con non-summoning mobs in Luclin.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=traigosode>TraigosOde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 11:56:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re</span><hr size=1> I think an ideal solution would be an improved decoy, one with a 100+ ds and 10k hp but low melee output.  That would give us a pet that we could use to solo, but it would not provide something unbalancing in groups.  <br>
